	<h1>About Mines View Park</h1>
	<img id = "image1" src="minesview.jpg" width = "750" height = "250"/>
		<p> Mines view park is one of the main attraction that makes tourists want to go back to Baguio City. 
		It’s located in a cliff where we’ll see a nice view of Baguio City’s mountainous slope and abandoned mines.
		From the observation deck of the park,a breathtaking panoramic view of Benguet's gold and copper mines 
		and the surrounding mountains unfolds before you. Mines View park is also near to other tourists destination 
		like the Mansion and Wright park. </p>
	
	<h2>Good Shepherd Convent</h2>
	<h5>You don't want to miss good shepherd when in Baguio!</h5>
	<img id = "image2" src="gshepherd.jpg" width = "auto" height= "250" />
		<p>You will find the Good Shepherd Convent in the Mines View Barangay. 
		The store is popularly known for the different products made by the Good Shepherd nuns and visitors coming up to the city. 
		Good Shepherd convent is a must place to go when you're already at mines view park because of their delicious "pasalubongs".</p>
		
	<h1>Human Rights Advocacy in Mines View Barangay</h1>
	<h3>No to death penalty!</h3>
	<img id = "image3" src="notodeath.jpg" width = "auto" height= "250" />
		<p>As we wander at Mines view park, we saw a lot of tarpaulins and posters that promotes human rights and one of them is 
		"No to death penalty, yes to life!". The program is being supported by the mines view barangay to promote fair justice. We all 
		do not want risking innocent people being excuted for the crime they didn't commit. 	</p>
	
	<h3>Work, Work, Work, Work, Work!</h3>
	<img id = "image4" src="labor.jpg" width = "auto" height= "150" />
	<img id = "image5" src="labor2.jpg" width = "auto" height= "150" />
		<p>In this part, Mines View Barangay did it right! We interviewed some of the vendors and we're happy to hear that they are
		receiving the minimum wage of 300 pesos in baguio.</p>
		
